text.tspan: Country cycle planning database, CAF, MICS 2003/Childinfo
This box and whiskers plot shows the distribution of values within regions and helps compare across regions. The bottom edge of each box represents the lower quartile within that region,
the upper edge represents the upper quartile. The dividing line in the box represents the median value. The whiskers at the top and bottom show the minimum and maximum values in that region.
